<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-14T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-14T16:36:00-05:00" n="677" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11988.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Florida. <lb/> Vera
                                    Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-14T15:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In reply to Department’s April 13, have received following from Mayo:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>No intimation received of existence of martial law or of
                                    objection to boat taking supplies. Stewards, orderlies, etc.,
                                    are going ashore when necessary. <pb facs="0575" n="459" xml:id="pg_459"/> Only part of boat’s crew out of boat to
                                    handle stores. Men were sailors, not marines.</p>
                                <p rend="right">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayo</hi>.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>